<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="68" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">
This species is distributed from the Pyrenees, across most of Europe up to 
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1082,187,213]" name="Japan" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[1099,1347,186,212]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[1219,1278,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). In the literature containing the records of 
<taxonomicName box="[602,733,222,248]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zygaenidae</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[773,855,222,248]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
the species is commonly cited (
<bibRefCitation author="Mann, J." box="[1225,1360,222,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="139 - 189" refId="ref9850" refString="Mann, J. (1857) Verzeichnis der im Jahre 1853 in der Gegend von Fiume gesammelten Schmetterlinge. Wiener entomologische Monatschrift, 1, 139 - 189." type="journal article" year="1857">Mann 1857</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mann, J." box="[1373,1432,222,248]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="63 - 76" refId="ref9880" refString="Mann, J. (1867) Schmetterlinge gesammelt im J. 1866 um Josefsthal in der croat. Militargrenze. Verhandlungen der zoologischbotanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 17, 63 - 76." type="journal article" year="1867">1867</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mann, J." box="[198,257,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="371 - 388" refId="ref9914" refString="Mann, J. (1869) Lepidopteren gesammelt wahrend dreier Reisen nach Dalmatien in den Jahren 1850, 1862 und 1868. Verhandlunden zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien, 19, 371 - 388." type="journal article" year="1869">1869</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vukotinovic, L." box="[267,471,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10944" refString="Vukotinovic, L. (1879) Fauna leptirah u okolisu Zagrebackom. Jugoslavenska akademija znanosti i umjetnosti, Zagreb, 129 pp." type="book" year="1879">Vukotinović 1879</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bohatsch, O." box="[482,652,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="31 - 50" refId="ref9266" refString="Bohatsch, O. (1892) Beitrage zur Lepidopteren-Fauna Slavoniens. Wiener Entomologischen Vereines, 1892, 31 - 50." type="journal article" year="1892">Bohatsch 1892</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Koca, Gj." box="[663,787,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 67" refId="ref9592" refString="Koca, Gj. (1901) Prilog fauni leptira (Lepidoptera) Hrvatske i Slavonije. Glasnik Hrvatskoga Naravoslovnoga Drustva, 13, 1 - 67." type="journal article" year="1901">Koča 1901</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rebel, H." box="[798,929,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="97 - 377" refId="ref10440" refString="Rebel, H. (1904) Studien uber die Lepidopterenfauna der Balkanlander. II. Teil. Bosnien und Herzegowina. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 19, 97 - 377." type="journal article" year="1904">Rebel 1904</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abafi-Aigner, L." box="[938,1154,258,284]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="71 - 105" refId="ref9169" refString="Abafi-Aigner, L. (1910) Adelek Magyar Tengermellek, Horvatorszag es Dalmaczia lepkefaunajahoz. Rovartani lapok, 17, 71 - 105." type="journal article" year="1910">Abafi-Aigner 1910</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mladinov, L." box="[1165,1339,258,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10000" refString="Mladinov, L. (1958) 1 Popis nocnih leptira (Noctua) Zagreba i okolice. Hrvatski narodni zooloski muzej, Zagreb, 61 pp." type="book" year="1958">Mladinov 1958</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Stauder, H." pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref10678" refString="Stauder, H. (1921) Die Zygaenidenarmut der adriatischen Inseln. Societas entomologica, 36, 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1921">Stauder 1921</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stauder, H." box="[268,327,294,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="35 - 39" refId="ref10700" refString="Stauder, H. (1932) Die Schmetterlingsfauna der illyro-adriatischen Festland- und Inselzone [Faunula Illiyro-Adriatica]. Entomologischen Anzeiger 12, 35 - 39 + 53 - 54 + 71 - 72 + 92 + 131 - 132 + 150 - 152 + 200 + 233 - 234 + 256." type="journal article" year="1932">1932</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Witt, T. J." box="[339,454,294,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="413 - 440" refId="ref10968" refString="Witt, T. J. (1987) Lepidopterologische Sammelergebnisse der Reisen Franz Daniels nach Istrien in den Jahren 1965 mit 1971 (Lepidoptera, Bombyces et Sphinges). Entomofauna, 8, 413 - 440." type="journal article" year="1987">Witt 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[466,657,294,323]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis box="[532,589,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). However, the last record from 
<collectingCountry box="[1019,1101,294,320]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
dates from 1971 (
<bibRefCitation author="Witt, T. J." box="[1306,1424,294,320]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" pagination="413 - 440" refId="ref10968" refString="Witt, T. J. (1987) Lepidopterologische Sammelergebnisse der Reisen Franz Daniels nach Istrien in den Jahren 1965 mit 1971 (Lepidoptera, Bombyces et Sphinges). Entomofauna, 8, 413 - 440." type="journal article" year="1987">Witt 1987</bibRefCitation>
). Accordingly, records present in this work are the first after almost 50 years. During this survey, the species was collected from four localities, within the known range in 
<collectingCountry box="[849,935,366,392]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
. As was stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[1146,1404,366,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[1264,1314,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al</emphasis>
. (1999)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Rhagades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">R. pruni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is missing from the Mediterranean region, which is true also for most of the coastal area of 
<collectingCountry box="[1293,1375,402,428]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,187,1846]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[151,1436,181,1858]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution of Rhagades pruni in Croatia based on newly collected data and historical records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643393" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4643393/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). During this survey, the species was recorded on both dry and wet grasslands. The occurrence of the species on different biotopes is already known (
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[638,877,474,500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[755,811,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). Caterpillars feed on 
<taxonomicName box="[1121,1294,475,500]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[1121,1294,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Prunus spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bertaccini &amp; Fiumi 1999)" baseAuthorityName="Bertaccini &amp; Fiumi" baseAuthorityYear="1999" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Calluna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Calluna vulgaris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bertaccini, E. &amp; Fiumi, G." box="[305,593,510,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" refId="ref9230" refString="Bertaccini, E. &amp; Fiumi, G. (1999) III Bombici e Sfingi d'Italia (Lepidoptera Zygenidae). Natura - Guiliano Russo Editore, Monterenzio (BO), 159 pp." type="book" year="1999">Bertaccini &amp; Fiumi 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Denis &amp; Schiffermuller" baseAuthorityYear="1775" box="[613,706,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Rhagades" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruni">
<emphasis box="[613,706,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">R. pruni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be regarded as rare and local in 
<collectingCountry box="[1121,1207,510,536]" name="Croatia" pageId="7" pageNumber="68">Croatia</collectingCountry>
. An effort should be done in order to expand the known distribution and asses the status of the known populations.
</paragraph>
